node_modules

# Local-only git backup folders — created when swapping .git directories.
# Contain pack files that may exceed GitHub's 100 MB blob limit; never push.
.git-nemlig-backup/
.git-original/

# mcp/node_modules is no longer committed — hooks/mcp-deps-install.js runs
# `npm install` on SessionStart to populate it. Two historical incidents
# shaped the current setup:
#
# 1. Pre-76f0b6b1 (TODO 0233f9c8): files WERE committed (pruned, ~6 MB) as an
#    offline-fallback. Git worktree merge cascades deleted random tracked
#    node_modules files in main, breaking subsequent worker spawns. Fix:
#    untrack mcp/node_modules entirely. First-boot now requires network.
#
# 2. Post-untrack (TODO 3d6b7587, 2026-05-20): The SessionStart hook previously
#    ran `npm ci`, which DELETES node_modules before reinstalling. On Windows,
#    when another process (worker, MCP server) holds open file handles to
#    anything in mcp/node_modules, the unlink syscall fails with EPERM
#    partway through. The deletion partially completes, the install never
#    finishes, and random packages (most often @anthropic-ai/claude-agent-sdk)
#    disappear. Fix: switched to `npm install` (incremental — never wipes the
#    tree) at hooks/mcp-deps-install.js. Recovery for already-corrupted
#    state: copy from plugin cache (docs/solutions/mcp-node-modules-sdk-
#    silently-removed-by-merge-cascade-recovery-from-plugin-cache.md).
dist
out
.DS_Store
.eslintcache
*.log*

# Root-only: the root package.json exists solely to host `npm test` — a
# casual `npm install` here would generate a lockfile we don't track.
# Nested lockfiles (mcp/, packages/forge-core/) are tracked and unaffected
# because this pattern is anchored with a leading slash.
/package-lock.json

